The '''''Ghana Medical Journal''''' is a quarterly [[Open access (publishing)|open-access]] [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[public health journal|medical journal]] from [[Ghana]]. It is published by the [[Ghana Medical Association]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ajol.info/index.php/gmj|title=Ghana Medical Journal|publisher=African Journals Online|accessdate=September 8, 2010}}</ref> and the current [[editor-in-chief]] is [[David Ofori-Adjei]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aibst.com/index.php/about-aibst/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&categoryId=45&id=113|title=Professor David Ofori-Adjei|publisher=Africa Institute of Biomedical Research and Technology|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707094641/http://www.aibst.com/index.php/about-aibst/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&categoryId=45&id=113|archivedate=2011-07-07|df=}}</ref> The journal is under the [[African Health Journals Partnership Project]] that is funded by the [[United States National Library of Medicine]] and the [[John E. Fogarty International Center]]. Full text of published articles are available on the journal's website and through [[African Journals OnLine]] and [[PubMed Central]].

